I’ve loved my @mynuface years. It’s been my secret weapon in achieving a sculpted and toned look naturally. As a new mom, I have even less time than I would like to admit for self-care, and this is why the NEW @mynuface TRINITY+ Smart Advanced Toning Device is now my best friend. With new innovative technology (3 depth technology that allows you to access 3 layers of your skin and muscle) and a “ boost” button that gives an extra 25% boost of microcurrent on your target areas (mine is the eyebrow and cheekbone area) I can give myself a microcurrent at home facial in 5 min with results that are incredible. The NuFACE app not only guides you through your personalized routine but is also your go to place for all things microcurrent. If you haven’t tried @mynuface yet I highly recommend it as the first step in your beauty/ facial wellness routine. I would love to hear what you think of the results, feel free and ask me questions in the comment section. #MyNuFACE @mynuface #NuFACEAmbassador

One of the best parts of being pregnant for me was having my hair! I loved having it thicker and fuller than it’s been in years. Now that’s I’m 4 months postpartum I’m more diligent than ever to keep as much of it as I can. Postpartum hair loss is normal and natural but that doesn’t mean I can’t help my body adjust easier to the hormonal changes in my body. My go to brands that show results are  @moonjuice Super Hair @vida_glow collagen and hair supplements, and @nutrafol . Not just for new mamas. For everyone because beauty starts from the inside out.

I’ve taken the last 5 months to greatly decrease the amount of time I’ve spent on social. Part of the change was due to becoming a new mom and finding balance in my priorities and time management. Questions of self worth came up, my relevance in the world, and the new identity I was now stepping into. Nothing prepares you for the love you feel for your child… and nothing prepares you for the woman you will become because of it. I’m excited to be back here with my community. Sharing my life and what I’m learning on the way. Thank you for coming with me on this journey. Here we go 2023

You’ve reorganized our lives and made being in the moment a priority. I’ve never loved harder than now. Thank you my little dove for opening my heart to a new deeper level. For making me stop and take time off of work, from whatever I used to call my normal, for challenging me to start a new life at 36, for helping me carve out different habits. She’s a little mermaid baby for sure. One of our favorite brands is @bambonatureusa. I discovered them in the baby isle of our local grocery store and was blown a away! They make incredible diapers ( more on that later ) and a whole line of skin care for little ones. For over 30 years @bambonatureusa has manufactures environmentally safe products earning the highest level of credentials, awards, eco labels  in the world. Effective and clean ensuring little ones sensitive skin is cared for. We use the Bath Buddy Hair and Body Wash for Ondine’s bath and it’s perfect for the whole family. Free from all the bad stuff ( dyes, harsh chemicals, etc) 100% vegan, and dermatological tested. Also affordable :) if you haven’t checked them out please do. No this isn’t an AD I’m just obsessed with the brand and the product line.

Happy International Women’s Day!!!!! Today is one of my favorite holidays. It’s celebrated with such respect in my homeland and a day I look forward to as much as New Year. Something I didn’t pay much attention to prior to giving birth is celebrating all of the women in me. The past 36 years of me and the places and things the “ women in me” gone and felt. Wow it’s been a journey. Today I’m celebrating all of those women. The little girl from a village in Russia ( a taxidermists daughter), the hell raiser that I was in my late 20’s, the actor and business woman, the heartbroken lost version of me in my early 30’s, the wife and now mother. I’ve realized that owning those parts of me is the freedom I’ve been looking for. Xxx 🤍🤍🤍🤍🤍🤍🤍🤍 sending love to all women

Hi there, let me introduce myself ( or reintroduce ) my name is Olesya. I’m an environmentalist, a creative director, poet and yes an actor. I grew up living off the land in what was then Soviet Russia  in a small village of 12 houses. ( yes I have some stories to tell … I’m writing them all down for you… in a book of essays ). Both my parents are taxidermists and I grew up skinning and stuffing animals all while also being a “ Disney star”. I’m an activist and Mother Earth advocate that yes can trap a rabbit and skin a deer. It’s a wild world and I live in place of duplicity. If you’ve followed me for some time thank you. I hope the films and tv shows I’ve acted in have brought you joy or simply entertainment. There is nothing more that I love than having helped others disappear into the world of fantasy for an hour or so. If you’re new to my page HI!!You can find me with my family ( husband @joeypauline and our babe Ondine , my mama who lives with us @nataliyainlosangeles ) living outside of Yosemite National Park doing all kinds of mountain people things 🤣 as well as me being an occasional tv/movie star walking red carpets and making magic.. but mostly I’m a woman that loves the planet deeply. I hope you find helpful tips on how to be more sustainable and green in an attainable and real way. I believe in the small steps to a better planet and a better you. It’s not all or nothing. I love me some Botox and yes most of my makeup is clean beauty. I don’t eat mammals but my husband does. It’s a balance and I’m here to help if I can when it comes to your questions. I know more about products and services than I’d like to admit and if I wasn’t an actor I would have been a CEO of a large company like @seventhgeneration. I’m your friendly actress that’s also a Guinea pig for all things sustainable/ beauty/ health. Xxxx LOVE you all.

When it came time to renovate our kitchen we were locked into the original small floor plan. This meant that the appliances we chose had to not only prepare beautiful meals but elevate the space. In our search we discovered @zlinekitchen and fell in love with the Autograph Edition Range. With a solid piece cast-iron grate, one-piece porcelain cooktop, handcrafted high quality Italian Burners, three layered glass oven, SmoothSlide ball bearing racks and dual lighting our @zlinekitchen range is the heart of the home. As powerful as it is beautiful with 4,200-18,000 BTU’s, the @zlinekitchen Autograph Edition Range is built to last. ( we chose champagne gold accents which in turn dictated the rest of the color choices in our kitchen). We chose the @zlinekitchen French Door Counter Depth Refrigerator for its elevated design and modern look. Made of 430 grade stainless steel and  ENERGY STAR certified, it includes a large fridge and freezer space (22.3 cu.ft capacity), adjustable shelving, two humidity controlled crisper drawers and 6 LED lights. To quote the founder of @zlinekitchen Andrew Zuro “ Luxury should never be left desired. It’s meant to be attainable”. Thank you @zlinekitchen for making a product line that makes even the smallest spaces feel grand.

Happy Earth Day! ( today and every day) this year our family chose to celebrate our beautiful earth by planting 2 acres of wildflowers in our deer Meadow. Creating a wild yard is an easy way to support your local pollinators and ensure the future of our own food sources. If you live in the city or simply have a small space please know that most pollinator, friendly plants are very happy, living in containers out of a window. It’s an all of the little ways that add up to make a difference. As a climate optimist, I believe together we truly can turn this around, we deserve a better future, so do our children,the bees,in all living things.

As a perfume lover it’s been more than challenging to find a scent that I love that’s also safe for my body. Perfumers keep the recipes of their scents a secret… which leads to some sexy mystery but also to using chemicals known to distrust your hormones and much more. Not so sexy now is it. That’s why I love @henryrose ( founded by @michellepfeifferofficial) they have done ALL of the work for their customers by ensuring that the ingredients they use are as clean as possible. They have 100% ingredient transparency because they want you to know what you are putting on your body … now that’s SEXY. Somehow out of the 3000 ingredients available to make scents they were able to reduce that number to only 300 options that were clean and safe. Making their scents complex, unique, and clean. 🤍🤍🤍 thank you @henryrose

It’s been 10 months since I’ve given birth and I’ve only now started moving my body daily. I wanted to share because the post birth journey is just that. A journey. It goes at the pace you set it and the most important thing is to prioritize what works for you. I’m so grateful I listened to my body because until now it has NOT wanted to be moved, be worked out, or rushed to do anything. No matter how much I missed all of my jeans or what society and my job as an actor may say about what I should look like … it’s my life and my delicate incredible female body. I’m beyond grateful to have had the opportunity to make a little human which means countless changes in all the ways that make me whole. I’ll go in more detail about my journey later but  for now I just wanted to say “ be gentle with yourself, you are your souls home”.

I use the whole line now and I can honestly say I’m noticing a big difference in over all health and strength of my hair. Go to @mynajeau to learn more about hair oiling, the magical olive oil they use in the products, and the sustainable pillars of the brand.

Water is one of our planet’s greatest resources and needs to be preserved. Did you know that 40/50 states in the US have a water shortage (1)? I’ve partnered with @finishdishwashing to spread awareness about their initiatives to help preserve our water supply. @finishdishwashing has recently unveiled their HOPEFUL MONUMENT, a work of art meant to never be seen. The HOPEFUL MONUMENT is meant to inspire action for the future and sits at the bottom of an at-risk lake, only to be seen if water levels drop low enough to reveal it. @finishdishwashing is also working with @wwf to replenish and preserve the Rio Grande, home to countless species of animals while supporting 16 million people with water (2). To learn more head to the @finishdishwashing site.

An easy way to help reduce your water usage at home is to #SkipTheRinse with Finish Quantum which tackles 24 hour dried-on stains with no pre-rinsing, saving up to 20 gallons of water every time, yes EVERY time. (3)
We are all in this together, and working together is exactly how we can ensure a better future for everyone. #Finishpartner #SkipTheRinse #HopefulMonument 

Data sources: 
(1) National Geographic, 2020
(2) Mexican National Institute for Statistics and Geography, INEGI (2010). Plassin et al (2020) 
(3) All water data sourced from www.epa.gov, Clear U&A, SGS and the US Census Bureau

One of my favorite parts of being a mother is being unapologetically authentic to my needs. Before, I would place my desires and needs last always making sure others were served first … Ondine has taught me that I MUST take care of myself first because if I don’t everyone will be effected. I can’t mother her to my fullest if I’m not feelings secure and stable. I can’t love on her and be present if I haven’t poured love on myself first. She also learns from my behavior and my actions not just my words. She sees that I care about my well-being and it teaches her that being a woman and mother doesn’t mean sacrificing who you are and what you need.
